HEADWORD: Niagara Falls
<hw>Niagara Falls</hw></mhw> <pos>prop. n.</pos>
<def>A large waterfall on the Niagara River near <city>Buffalo</city>
remarkable for the volume and constancy of the water flowing over it.
That part of the waterfall in Canada is the Horseshoe Falls; the U. S.
portion is called the American Falls.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

